{
  "name": "RPlog_Defense_of_Farlex",
  "title": "The Defense of Farlex",
  "summary": "On the besieged mining world of Farlex, the aging Imperial commander Danik Kreldin makes a last stand in the bombarded capital of Morai, directing his dug-in troops, traps, and artillery from an underground bunker. The New Republic assault, coordinated by the Horansi Captain Snal'Fashtalli ('Snarl') with sniper Master Sergeant Sandor Woden feeding intelligence to the Imperials and Corporal Whorus rigging the streets with grisly traps and explosives, pushes in on all four gates at once. As Y-wings, Pathfinders under First Sergeant Giran Blaine, and ground troops breach the defenses, Kreldin unleashes brutal tactics: a high-frequency siren that incapacitates the non-human attackers, and waves of light-bearing civilians driven into the rebel guns to expose their firing positions. The Horansi rally their stricken troops by filtering out the siren and answer with thermal detonators, and despite ferocious house-to-house fighting the Imperials are slowly forced back. With the northern gate fallen and his forces whittled to a final stand at the plaza and capitol, Kreldin orders evacuation transport readied as the New Republic advances toward victory.",
